 for them. I don't take it off because they start in a good school. Public schools do not allow religion an some to the point where Christmas cannot be enjoyed. Funny but we had a friend who almost in a mad tone made the following comment &quot; I wish we could afford to put our child in a private school too&quot; to which my wife quickly responded with &quot;We don't have a $700.00 a month SUBURBAN payment!&quot; Its called priorites and many parents don't have them. Further if more parents chose their children to go to private schools that could afford it, there would be less over crowded classrooms making the public schools therefore better. Incredibly some parents won't send their kids to private school because they do not want to be viewed as eleatist! Ridiculous as is this article. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1086" language="en" documentId="3868" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="larry donoho" date="Aug 29, 2013 6:22PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="39" thumbsDown="0" origId="3868" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1086"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>